See [dbfiddle](https://dbfiddle.uk/?rdbms=mysql_8.0&amp;fiddle=ee1ff536cd722f2715e18e45322b4727).

If you really need to use the stored procedure you can do something like:

&lt;!-- language: lang-sql --&gt;

    DELIMITER //

    DROP PROCEDURE IF EXISTS `new_procedure`//
    
    CREATE PROCEDURE `new_procedure`()
    BEGIN
      DECLARE `rowCount`, `currentRow` BIGINT UNSIGNED;
      DECLARE `boundryData` LONGTEXT;
      DECLARE `updatedBoundry` POLYGON;
    
      SET `rowCount` := (
        SELECT COUNT(*)
        FROM `tbl_kml_data`
      );
      SET `currentRow` := 1;
    
      `myUpdateLoop`: WHILE (`currentRow` &lt;= `rowCount`) DO
        SET `boundryData` := (
          SELECT ST_AsText(`boundry`)
          FROM `tbl_kml_data`
          WHERE `tbl_id` = `currentRow`
        );
        -- SET `updatedBoundry` := ST_GeomFromText(&#39;POLYGON((6.546269854000059 80.15311213900003,6.54627481600005 80.15298415800004,6.54605968900006 80.15315188800008,6.546251038000038 80.15310380500006,6.546269854000059 80.15311213900003))&#39;);
        -- SET `updatedBoundry` := ST_GeomFromText(`boundryData`);
    
        UPDATE `tbl_kml_data`
        SET `f_polygon` = ST_GeomFromText(`boundryData`)
        WHERE `tbl_id` = `currentRow`;
    
        SET `currentRow` = `currentRow` + 1;
      END WHILE `myUpdateLoop`;
    END//

    DELIMITER ;

See [dbfiddle](https://dbfiddle.uk/?rdbms=mysql_8.0&amp;fiddle=ffd1738a18b7abd8f9a7630af6ae658c).

It is important to indicate the difference between [9.4 User-Defined Variables](https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/user-variables.html) and routine variables [13.1.17 CREATE PROCEDURE and CREATE FUNCTION Syntax](https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/create-procedure.html), are different variables (`@boundryData` != `boundryData`).

