I&#39;m not super clear on what you&#39;re trying to accomplish, but that error is happening because you&#39;re passing in each value in your column to your function as `t`, and then trying to use that float value as the parameters of `range` (which must be integers)

if you&#39;re trying to multiply each value in the column by the next 40 values in the column, maybe something like this:

    def fwdreturn(returns, start_index):
        outp = 1
        for i in range(0, 40):
            outp = outp * returns[start_index + i]
        return outp
    df[&#39;10 Year Fwd Return&#39;] = [fwdreturn(df[&#39;Q Return&#39;].to_list(), idx) for idx in range(0, df[&#39;Q Return&#39;].size)]
